        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>SENSITIVITY REQUIREMENTS:
The scientific goal of the proposal is to compare the fragmentation level assessed with current pre-ALMA interferometers in massive dense cores, with respect to the level assessed with ALMA, in order to search for any hidden population of low-mass fragments. Sensitivities of pre-ALMA interferometers are typically around 1~mJy/beam, which corresponds, for the typical distances of the proposed massive dense cores, to a mass sensitivity around 0.5 Msun. However, this mass sensitivity was inferred using a dust opacity law with an intrinsic uncertainty of up to a factor of 5. Thus, we require to reach a rms noise about a factor fo 20 better than the rms noise reached in pre-ALMA interferometers, which corresponds to about 50 microJy/beam. Using a total bandwidth of 7.4 GHz, the corresponding time per source is ~7 min. Taking into account that two of the targets are closer than 10 deg, the total amount of observing time requested for this project is 1h 48min.

IMAGING:
The pre-ALMA interferometric observations of the four proposed cores reveal fragments within 20-30''. Thus, the primary beam of ALMA at Band 6, of ~27'', covers well the region of interest of each core. 

CORRELATOR SETUP:
Observations will be carried out in dual polarization mode, using two basebands in low-resolution TDM mode, and two basebands in FDM mode. The TDM basebands will cover 2GHz each, while for each of the two FDM basebands we will use one window with a bandwidth of 1.875 GHz, providing a spectral resolution of 1.3 km/s. The two basebands in FDM are placed covering the CO(2-1) (outflow tracer), and C18O(2-1) (envelope/disk tracer), in order to exploit all the  capabilities of ALMA, and given that our targets strongly emit in these transitions. Overall, the total available bandwidth for the continuum is ~7.4 GHz.

CALIBRATION:
No special requirements. Just noting that he total time suggested by the OT is 1h 48min to observe 4 targets 7 min on-source each target (i.e., 28 minutes of total on-source time). The total requested time could probably be decreased if the targets were grouped in pairs according to their LST range, and observed each pair in the same scheduling block.

DATA RATE:
The data rate for this proposal is below 6 MB/s.</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
